1Ô∏è‚É£ What is UID and GID?

Answer:
UID = User ID
GID = Group ID
They uniquely identify users and groups on the system.

2Ô∏è‚É£ What is the difference between useradd & adduser?

Answer:

useradd ‚Üí low-level command (default on all Linux)

adduser ‚Üí high-level interactive script (Debian/Ubuntu)

3Ô∏è‚É£ How do you add a user to multiple groups?
sudo usermod -aG group1,group2,group3 username

4Ô∏è‚É£ What is /etc/passwd used for?

Answer:
Stores user account info such as username, UID, GID, shell.

5Ô∏è‚É£ What is /etc/shadow used for?

Answer:
Stores password hashes and password expiry details (secure).

6Ô∏è‚É£ How do you check user password expiry?
chage -l username

7Ô∏è‚É£ How do you lock/unlock a user account?

Lock:

passwd -l username


Unlock:

passwd -u username

8Ô∏è‚É£ How do you delete a user with home directory?
userdel -r username

9Ô∏è‚É£ What is a primary and secondary group?

Primary group ‚Üí created when a user is created

Secondary groups ‚Üí additional groups for privileges

üîü How do you create a group and assign a user to it?
groupadd dev
usermod -aG dev username
